# Nucleus log rotation (ADR-020) — rendered by tools/launchd/install.sh
# (__WORKSPACE_ROOT__ / __USER__ substituted) into /etc/newsyslog.d/nucleus.conf.
#
# macOS runs newsyslog as root hourly at :30 (com.apple.newsyslog), so the
# root-owned caddy.log rotates fine alongside the user-owned agent logs.
#
# Flags: G = logfilename is a glob; B = binary (no ASCII rotation banner —
# these logs are tailed/grepped by healthcheck.sh and the dashboard); N =
# no process to signal (don't HUP syslogd).
#
# Z (gzip) is DELIBERATELY omitted: KeepAlive daemons (discord, whatsapp,
# nucleus-dashboard, bonsai, caddy) hold their launchd StandardOutPath fd
# in append mode across rotation and keep writing into the renamed .0 file
# until their next restart — gzip+unlink would silently destroy those
# writes. Uncompressed archives preserve them, at a trivial disk cost
# (1MB live + 5 archives ≈ 6MB cap per service).
#
# size is in KB: rotate past 1MB, keep 5 archives.
#
# logfilename                       [owner:group]   mode count size when flags
__WORKSPACE_ROOT__/memory/*.log     __USER__:staff  644  5     1024 *    GBN
